value.0: Bearing an open visor and a hand and a half sword, this lovingly crafted statue of Helm projected a strange sensation that made you feel as if you were being watched. For those who reflect deeply upon the statue, a strong sense of diligence avails itself to them.
This finely crafted suit of full plate mail has been fitted lovingly for a Watcher; a priest of Helm.
Piecemeal or complete armors of this type offer protection equivalent to a suit of full plate armor.
A hand and a half sword consecrated in the rituals of Helm, He of the Unsleeping Eyes.
These fine tower shields are said to be blessed by Helm.
The chains on these floor-bound shackles are chipped and marked as if someone had been pounding on them with a rock. Whoever it was, it doesn't appear that their efforts met with any success.

Smooth and exotic silk sheets line this mattress which is stuffed with some material that feels as if your sleeping on a cloud. Top qualty wool and cotton comforters, washed to a point that they feel extremely soft, with satiny smooth pillows for a perfect head rest, complete this package. Resting here would be akin to a blessing from the gods.

A plain cot with a few old blankets tosses on it as a makeshift mattress and another rolled up as a pillow, doesn't seem that inviting, Yet it's better than sleeping on the floor and allows one a fairly decent nights rest.
